## 3. Proto Definition

Add your domain message types and RPC definitions to `Protos/{{ model.manifest.service_name }}.proto`:

```protobuf
syntax = "proto3";

option csharp_namespace = "{{ model.names.namespace }}";

package {{ model.manifest.service_name | string.replace "-" "_" }};

service {{ model.names.dot_net_class_name }}Service {
  rpc Get (GetRequest) returns (RecordResponse);
  rpc Create (CreateRequest) returns (RecordResponse);
  rpc Update (UpdateRequest) returns (RecordResponse);
  rpc Delete (DeleteRequest) returns (DeleteResponse);
  rpc List (ListRequest) returns (stream RecordResponse);
}

message GetRequest {
  string id = 1;
}

message CreateRequest {
  string reference = 1;
  string submitted_by = 2;
  int64 submitted_at_unix = 3;
}

message UpdateRequest {
  string id = 1;
  string status = 2;
  string notes = 3;
}

message DeleteRequest {
  string id = 1;
}

message DeleteResponse {
  bool success = 1;
}

message RecordResponse {
  string id = 1;
  string reference = 2;
  string status = 3;
  int64 created_at_unix = 4;
  int64 updated_at_unix = 5;
}

message ListRequest {
  int32 page = 1;
  int32 page_size = 2;
}
```

**Proto conventions:**
- Use `snake_case` for field names in proto
- Use `int64` for timestamps (Unix milliseconds) — never proto `Timestamp` for Pervaxis services
- Keep proto messages flat — avoid deep nesting

